Nov 15 2006 	SMALL rooms at Hotel Griffon!	Hotel Griffon has a cute charm to it, but I would only stay here again if the price was very low and I was not planning on spending a lot of time in the room. Pros:Cute, historic charm. Nice exposed brick wall in room and great Aveda bath products. Good location, although we usually had to walk a block or two to get a cab. Continental breakfast was nice. Everything appeared very clean. I requested more towels and they were sent up quickly. We were very impressed with all of the staff, including the front desk, in the restaurant, and at breakfast. Cons:Many people said small rooms, which usually dont bother me, but our room was beyond small. I actually felt a little claustrophobic because the window looked out into a very small, dark, dirty brick cave-like hole. There are also very few king beds because many of the rooms are too small to accommodate them. Despite booking months in advance and requesting a king bed multiple times, I could only get a full bed. The rooms must also be all different sizes because I was with other people who paid the same rate and both had slightly larger rooms so you may get the luck of the draw on your room. The sink and mirror in the room was a little strange but at least there was good counter space. The location of the TV mounted on the wall was just too high and awkward. The bed and linens were below average and the pillows were definitely very old, as they were extremely flat. The shower had very low water pressure. In fact, I think the sink faucet had more water flow and pressure than the shower.I was on the third floor, close to the elevator and the stairs, right above the fireplace downstairs and there was a definite smell in the hallway that other people wrote about, but I couldn't smell it in the room. I could however, very clearly hear every word being spoken in the hallway, even when I could tell that people were trying to be quiet. There was also a substantial gap between the door and the floor which let in a lot of light in the night. Lastly, the temperature controls were not very good. Sometimes the room was too hot and sometimes too cold and the basic warm/cool control in the room did very little to change the temperature. Verdict: Hotel Griffon tries very hard, but is average. It is probably better to stay in an upgraded, guaranteed King room with a view, but for those prices I would just stay somewhere else, especially with two people in a room. Don't even think about roll away beds or having kids with you!	
